The paper deals with preserving privacy in binary datasets, which is a common concern in database systems (cs.DB) and security (cs.CR). The methodology used involves inducing decision trees (cs.LG) and hiding sensitive classification rules (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses some key lemmas related to the hiding process, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
